  • Method Details

    • getQuadrantClusterAt

      public List<Quadrant> getQuadrantClusterAt(int x, int y)
      Get a List of Quadrants adjacent to one with the given x,y inclusive of the one at the given coordinates. As an example if you pass in 1,1 it should get the Quadrants (if they exist) at: 0,0 - top left corner 1,0 - top center 2,0 - top right 0,1 - center left 1,1 - center 2,1 - center right 0,2 - bottom left 1,2 - bottom center 2,2 - bottom right
      Parameters:
      x - - x coordinate of the center quadrant for the cluster.
      y - - y coordinate of the center quadrant for the cluster.
      Returns:
      a List of Quadrants adjacent to one with the given x,y inclusive of the one at the given coordinates.

    • generateQuadrants

      public List<Quadrant> generateQuadrants()

      Returns:
      a List of Quadrants
